query: Are there different visa requirements for people from different countries to attend the conference in Macau?
output: Yes, there are different visa requirements for people from different countries to attend the conference in Macau. Most countries can travel to Macau visa-free or obtain a visa upon arrival. However, visitors from Bangladesh, Nepal, Nigeria, Pakistan, Sri Lanka and Vietnam are required to apply for a visa in advance through a Chinese embassy or consulate. Visitors from Mainland China can apply for an Exit-Entry Permit for Travelling to and from Hong Kong and Macao to travel to Macau for up to seven days. Non-residents of Macao are required to have a valid passport and "entry permit" or "visa" except for certain exceptions.

query: What are the restrictions or requirements for canceling conference registration?
output: All cancellations must be sent to registration@ijcai.org via email. Any name changes will be dealt as a cancellation and a new registration. No refund will be made for cancellations received after July 19, 2023 or for registrants who fail to attend in person. For cancellations made until July 19, 2023, payments will be refunded minus a U$ 100 processing fee. This fee applies to all cancellations.

query: What is the application procedure to become a Student Volunteer for IJCAI 2023?
output: The application procedure to become a Student Volunteer for IJCAI 2023 involves submitting the IJCAI-23 Volunteer and Grant Application Form and accompanying documents via email to grants-volunteers-chairs-23@ijcai.org, no later than May 19, 2023. The documents to be sent per email must include a letter of support from the applicant’s advisor/head of department. The application form can be found at this link: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScBiwscNYmF38-AZ1ETKaPEIlurl_GigN009ox0GUyQeBpxeg/viewform. It is important to note that if you are applying, do not register and pay the registration fee until you are notified.

query: How to apply for the Travel and Accessibility Grant?
output: To apply for the IJCAI-AIJ 2023 Travel and Accessibility Grant, applicants must submit the IJCAI-23 Travel Grant Application Form along with accompanying documents via email to grants-volunteers-chairs-23@ijcai.org. The documents that must be included are: information on whether any other sources of support are available to the applicant, the results of approaching the department/local AI Society for support, and for students only, a letter of support from the applicant’s advisor/head of department. All documents must be submitted no later than May 19, 2023, midnight, AoE.

query: What are the requirements for proof of student status during student registration?
output: The proof of student status must be clearly readable in English language, contain the name of the candidate and the dates of validity. It must not fail verification. Student ID’s without clear dates of validity, webpage screenshots and unofficial records will not be accepted as proof. The validity of the proof must overlap with conference dates. However, postdocs and part-time students don't qualify for student discount at IJCAI2023.
